    <title>HTML Comments and Special Characters</title>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1 align="center">HTML Comments and Special Characters</h1>
    
        <p align="center">This document demonstrates how to use HTML comments and special characters using HTML entities.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Special Characters</h2>
        <p>Here are some special characters and their corresponding HTML entities:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>&amp;</strong> - Ampersand: &amp;</li>
            <li><strong>&lt;</strong> - Less-than sign: &lt;</li>
            <li><strong>&gt;</strong> - Greater-than sign: &gt;</li>
            <li><strong>&copy;</strong> - Copyright symbol: &copy; 2024</li>
            <li><strong>&reg;</strong> - Registered trademark symbol: &reg; Example Brand</li>
            <li><strong>&trade;</strong> - Trademark symbol: &trade; Example Product</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Form Example</h2>
       
        <form action="#" method="post">
            <table border="1" width="50%" align="center" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
              
                <tr>
                    <td align="right"><b>Name:</b></td>
                    <td><input type="text" name="name" size="30" placeholder="Enter your name" required></td>
                </tr>

         
                <tr>
                    <td align="right"><b>Email:</b></td>
                    <td><input type="email" name="email" size="30" placeholder="Enter your email" required></td>
                </tr>

       
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="2" align="center">
                      
                        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </form>
    </section>

    <footer>
     
        <p align="center">&copy; 2024 HTML Examples. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

